case_vignette: A 3-year-old girl was brought to the emergency department with a 2-month history of a white pupil and a 1-day history of redness and pain in the right eye. An eye examination showed leukocoria, as well as iris neovascularization and a white, nodular mass in the posterior chamber. The left eye was normal. B-scan ultrasonography showed calcification of the mass and vitreous seeding in the affected eye.
